===Etymology 1===
[[File:White Cat Nursing Four Kittens.jpg|right|thumb|A mother cat and her kittens]]
From {{inh|en|enm|moder}}, from {{inh|en|ang|mōdor}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*mōdēr}} (compare {{cog|fy|moer}}, {{cog|stq|Muur}}, {{cog|nl|moeder}}, {{cog|de|Mutter}}, {{cog|da|moder}}, {{cog|no|mor}}), from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*méh₂tēr}} (compare {{cog|ga|máthair}}, {{cog|la|mater}}, {{cog|sq|motër||sister}}, {{cog|xto|mācar}}, {{cog|txb|mācer}}, {{cog|lt|mótė}}, {{cog|ru|мать}}, {{cog|grc|μήτηρ}}, {{cog|hy|մայր}}, {{cog|fa|مادر|tr=mâdar}}, {{cog|sa|मातृ|tr= mā́tṛ}}). Superseded non-native {{cog|enm|mere|t=mother}} borrowed from {{cog|fro|mere|t=mother}}.

Some authorities consider the sense "greatest thing of its kind" to be a {{calque|en|ar|أُمّ||mother|nocap=1}}, but others do not<ref>{{R:MWO}}</ref> and other familial terms are also used this way, e.g. ''[[granddaddy]]''.

